[MUTATION LOG]  (run_quant_loop discovery cycle, 2026-06-24)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
iter 0  TrendMA(50,200) baseline ............. OOS S=0.70  DD=33.7%  RE-RUN
        flaw: fixed slow MA rides the whole COVID crash; fails both gates.
        mutate: replace with an adaptive, lookback-free Kalman trend.

iter 1  Kalman local-linear-trend ENSEMBLE ... OOS S=1.11  DD=15.2%  RE-RUN
        (6 speeds, sign-averaged; single speeds are fragile OOS spikes.)
        flaw: trend-only Sharpe-limited; whipsaw in chop, DD at the limit.
        mutate: add a weakly-correlated alpha (Kalman mean-reversion).

iter 2  + Kalman-level MEAN-REVERSION blend .. OOS S=1.15  DD=11.4%  RE-RUN
        (0.6 trend / 0.4 dip-buy, uptrend-gated; corr ~0.37, DD halved.)
        flaw: diversification works but Sharpe still 0.05 short of 1.2.
        mutate: add a risk overlay for the stress periods (2020, 2022).

iter 3  + Kalman ^VIX-slope RISK OVERLAY ..... OOS S=1.21  DD= 8.4%  ALPHA FOUND*
        de-risk smoothly when implied vol is rising; slippage-robust (clears
        1.2 even with +1 day execution lag). *Frictionless pass.

--- Friction regime: runner now charges 1 bp per unit position change ----------
iter 4  (iter-3 strategy, costs ON) .......... OOS S=1.197 DD= 8.5%  RE-RUN
        flaw: turnover 203 — the continuous VIX risk-scaler re-trades every bar;
        1 bp/turn costs ~0.014 Sharpe. mutate: cut turnover without losing edge.
        [mutation done on the `maker` git worktree, then merged to master.]

iter 5  + 0.15 position DEADBAND ............. OOS S=1.24  DD= 8.4%  ALPHA FOUND
        hold position; re-trade only when target moves >= 0.15 notional. Turnover
        203->144; deadband also removes noise trades (net S 1.24 > frictionless
        1.21). Robust: net S >= 1.2 for any band in [0.10, 0.20]. PASS.

Dead ends ruled out (do not retry): long/short trend, realized-vol targeting,
  VIX-level gating, continuous trend-magnitude sizing, adaptive-AR sleeve,
  hysteresis/deadband, trim-when-extended. All scored below the iter-3 blend.
